content: Really cool concept for a new take on the horror genre that ends up feeling more like a stealth game. The game is also quite repetitive in spite of levels bringing different ideas as there's a lot of throw-a-rock-there-to-lure-the-enemies-away. The game was fun at first but later on felt more frustrating than fun with controls that have a tendency to confuse taps and swipes resulting in many undeserved deaths. The main mechanic could've also been used better as you forget about it after a while.
I absolutely loved this game. Here I am coming back to it for another play through 3 years later.

One of the most original games I have played. The game is able to tap into our primal instinct of fear very effectively. What you can't see is what makes you afraid the most. Incredible how such a minimalistic game can evoke such deep emotions.

I cannot praise this game enough. Forcing the player to cope with a totally dark environment creates a unique and challenging experience with a bit of spooky fun thrown in. The vagueness of the red threats makes them much more intimidating than any fully-rendered monster; the darkness combined with their eerie sound allows the imagination to run wild. The one minor complaint is that the game occasionally misinterprets a stealth move as a regular walk and you blow your cover without meaning to. However, I suspect this is either inherent in touch-screen inexactitude or user error on my part. An awesome concept well-realized.

I could've gave this game 5 stars for its unique concept alone, but I'm not because of its "read sensitive log data" permission which is one of the most dangerous permissions on Android since it could read other apps' data as well and, coupled with the Internet access permission, provides a backdoor to leak the user's private info. There is absolutely no valid reason for this permission! This is a GAME, not a system control app! Or is this a Trojan horse as well?
replyContent:
Hi Kevin, 
The read logs permission is so we can debug crashes that would otherwise be impossible for us to fix. Please visit www.acra.ch to learn more. Once all the outstanding issues are fixed we won't need the permission and it will be removed.
Thanks for playing!

Just updated today. So it says the immerse mode is added? Whats it? And I cant find crash reporting either. I have done both the black and white versions of the 40 stages already.
replyContent:
Hi Hui,

Immersive mode is for devices without any hardware buttons. It will hide the home/back buttons displayed on the screen so it won't interfere with the game. Crash reporting is so that we can identify and fix future crashes if they ever happen. Nothing new has been added gameplay-wise.

Thanks for playing!
